snippet.textDisplay: I feel like some people are too hard on this movie before it even released. I feel like the title connected is more symbolic than “ the Mitchell’s vs the machines”. That’s a really boring title and connected sounds cool. And if it was just about a dad reconnecting with his daughter, and going on a trip we have seen that trope of a parent scared of losing a relationship with their kid. And I like the robot stuff it makes this movie so much more action packed and I think combining a lot in this movie is a smart move. We just have to wait and see but this looks like a good movie already and the animation is just gorgeous

I don't think they were trying to "phone bad" us. I think it was just supposed to emphasize that as people get older, they get distant, and sometimes others don't want to lose that spark.

The father loves his daughter and doesn't want to feel like he isn't a piece of her life anymore.
